{"word":"ἐχθρός","slug":"ἐχθρός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐχθρός</b></el> <el>(ἐχθρός, ή, όν) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἔχθος'><el>ἔχθος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>hated, hateful</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>ἐχθρόν μοί ἐστιν</el>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a>, <i>'tis hateful</i> to me to . . , <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <i>hostile, at enmity with</i>, <el>τινι</el> <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b>as <a href='S:Substantive'>Subst.</a>, <el>ἐχθρός, ὁ</el>, <i>one's enemy</i>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>ὁ Διὸς ἐχθρός</el> <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>; <el>οἱ ἐμοὶ ἐχθροί</el> <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>IV. </b>the <a href='S:regular, regularly'>regul.</a> <a href='S:Comparative'>comp.</a> and <a href='S:Superlative'>Sup.</a> <el>ἐχθρότερος, -τατος</el> are rare: the <a href='S:irregular'>irreg.</a> <el>ἐχθίων, ἔχθιστος</el> being more used.<p/></div><div class='li500'><b>V. </b><a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>ἐχθρῶς</el>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <a href='S:Comparative'>comp.</a> <el>ἐχθροτέρως</el>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}